contentrichtext.text: '''Zaz''' may refer to: ==Places== *[[İzbırak, Midyat]], or Zaz, a village in Turkey *[[Zaz-e Gharbi Rural District]], an administrative subdivision of Iran *[[Zaz-e Sharqi Rural District]], an administrative subdivision of Iran *ZAZ, the IATA airport code for [[Zaragoza Airport]] in Spain *[[Zaragoza]] (ZAZ is often used as an abbreviation) ==Music== *[[Zaz (singer)]], stage name of French singer Isabelle Geffroy * "Zaz Turned Blue," a song from the 1983 Was (Not Was) album ''[[Born to Laugh at Tornadoes]]'' ==Others== *[[ZAZ]], a Ukrainian automobile manufacturer *[[Zucker, Abrahams and Zucker]], an American comedy film-making trio *[[ZAZ (TV channel)]], a defunct children-oriented cable channel from Mexico *Zaz, a former Brazilian Internet service provider now part of [[Terra Networks]] *[[Zaz (computer game)]], Zaz ain't Z is an arcade action think-fast game {{disambig|geo}}
